headline: Humana (OM:HUM) Net Margin Doubles to 2%, Reinforcing Recovery Narrative Despite Caution on Sustainability
summary: Humana (OM:HUM) reported net profit margins of 2%, an increase from 1.1% a year ago, and delivered a sharp year-on-year earnings growth of 93.6% after several years of declines averaging 12.2% per year. The company’s stock currently trades at SEK46, notably below its estimated fair value of SEK163.72, while its price-to-earnings ratio stands at just 10.8x compared to industry averages of 18.9x and 27.2x for peers. Looking ahead, analysts forecast earnings growth of 12.8% per year, outpacing...
